Industrial and systems engineers are often faced with decision-making under uncertainty, which requires the ability to characterize uncertainty. This course introduces students to models and methods based on stochastic processes, with a focus on engineering applications. Upon completion of this course, the learner will be able to:

• Be able to model and analyze uncertainty in real-world engineering problems;
• be able to formulate and solve probabilistic models that capture the essential elements of an engineering problem;
• be able to interpret the model solution to assist in engineering decision-making;
• be able to evaluate systems in a wide variety of applications using analytical and simulation-based methods.
